<br>
Nonetheless, think about this - is it possible that anti-war protestors have caused the forthcoming war in Iraq to happen?  Think about it for a moment.<br>
<br>
If the world had a united front when confronting Iraq, even Saddam would have realized that the other arab countries asking him to go into exile might have a good point.  Odds are he would have cooperated fully realizing that he was isolated from the rest of the world, and it's likely we wouldn't have to have a full-scale military conflict.<br>
<br>
However, with all the anti-war rallies around the globe, they have caused Saddam to see weakness.  With thousands of people around the globe protesting a possible war (and therefor basically agreeing that what Saddam is doing is okay), he has been emboldened, and with Franch holding up a new UN resolution, he believes that the worlds popular support is leaning toward him.  Of course this makes him far more uncooperative since he thinks he can get away with it, which means the US and UK have no diplomatic options left, and they have to act militarily.<br>
